10/08/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- UNMIK is sending 500 additional international police officers to northern Kosovo, to support the Kosovo Police Service and boost the security of residents in the area. UNMIK Acting Police Commissioner Wayne Hisson announced the decision on Wednesday (9 August), adding that the deployment was at the request of authorities in municipalities with a predominantly Serbian population. 
Also Wednesday, Mitrovica police said they had arrested a local Albanian, suspected of stabbing 18-year old Serb Ljubisa Janackovic in the village of Priluzje last week. The name of the suspect has not been released. (Politika - 10/08/06; KosovaLive, Tanjug - 09/08/06)
